ILLINOIS COAL: THE LEGACY OF AN INDUSTRIAL SOCIETY 
Allison, coal miner, recalls working conditions, hazards, pay, and relations between co-workers in Christian County, Illinois. He also discusses work done at the mine, reaction to the Progressive Miners movement, mechanization, and the problems of unemployment and obtaining insurance. 1 tape, 90 min., 15 pp. 
Interview by Kevin Corley, 1986 
